Question:-)You need to trigger an API call to an external system whenever a Liferay Object entry is created. What approach will you use?
Answer:-)I will use an Object Action (Webhook) to call the external API when an Object entry is created...

Question:)how you will genarte token in fragmnet and cx?
Answer:-)In Fragments, we use Liferay.authToken,
which is generated by Liferay during page rendering and 
automatically made available to the browser for secure backend API calls

:-)In Client Extensions, I will use OAuthApplicationHeadlessServer and OAuthApplicationAgent,
which are configured in the client-extension.yaml file for securing API calls

Question:)if you want to save a entry in objetc in which two or more attachment are there .
if there are more than 2 attachemnet adding day my day according to requiremnmt how you will do?
Answer:)I will create a parent object and a child object for attachments, 
then link them with a one-to-many relationship. This allows me to add multiple attachments dynamically as needed.

Question:)difference between types of token  in microservcie cx?
Answer:)I know The two Token's 
1)oAuthApplicationHeadlessServer-OAuthApplicationHeadlessServer is used when external apps or frontend need to call Liferay Headless APIs.
2)oAuthApplicationAgent-OAuthApplicationAgent is used for backend-to-backend calls or system integrations without user interaction





